{"original text":"@joser916: Have you tried installing the version linked a mere three posts above?\nit works hell ya i got my lil toy back!\nSomething aint right. I updated Firefox 1.5.0.1. Had to make Super D&G compatible. Wheras it worked fine before the Firefox update, I had to diable it cos it kept causing Firefox to freeze which in turn caused everything else to lock up. About 6 manual reeboots later only by disabling this one extension did everything else work OK. Boy, I miss this extension - it was sooooooooo good. Update please!\nI want to replace default directional search engines with my favorite ones.\nI've changed superdragandgo-0.2.6.xpi to superdragandgo-0.2.6.zip -> unpacked -> 'chrome' folder -> changed superdrag.jar to superdrag.zip -> unpacked -> 'content' folder -> edited superdrag.js -> what is next?\nI've tried to create .zip and then change to .jar but seems it doesn't work since when installing I get an error: Install script not found. How to create .jar file?\nrozin wrote: I want to replace default directional search engines with my favorite ones.\nA .jar file is just a .zip file with a different extension.\n1. Did you put the .jar file back in the chrome directory of the .XPI file?\n2. Did you accidentally delete the install.rdf and\/or chrome.manifest file that should exist in the root of the .XPI file?\nYou should put things back EXACTLY where you found them. The directory structure is very important.\nAs I've mentioned in some other thread, (generic) you should use a shell extension or utility like WinZIP or WinRAR that makes .ZIP (and hence .JAR and .XPI) archives look like regular subdirectories. This way you can see where exactly you are drag'n'dropping things. I use Total Commander personally.\nforeword: i posted this on the website on the formular, but the text seemed not to be formatted, so i came here and posted it -formatted- again.\n-same as above for text.\nplease tell me, what do you think.\nThere is a bug dragging links formatted as display:block. See testcase here.\nFor Super DragAndGo on Mac OS X, Is there a special format in specifying the directory where 'dragged' images are saved? This is when bypassing the 'use download manager' option in the preferences.\nI've tried different combinations of filepaths with preceding slashes\/drivenames\/etc and I'm having no luck.\nHow do I disable drag to left open in background and right foreground, which it seems to only do to images.\nIt seems that the searchbox API has been totally reworked in Firefox 2, and as a result, SDAG's drag-to-search feature is broken with Firefox 2. I took 0.2.6 (non-directional) and redid the drag-and-search code so that it works now with Firefox 2's new searchbox implementation.\nCan somebody please do as code65536 mentions on that web page (code diffs, etc.) and find a good version of the directional SuperDragandGo with security patch and apply his modifications to make it work with Firefox 2? If someone does so it could probably be hosted on that same site and people would have their choice of if they want directional or not.\nP.S. Thanks very much code65536 for fixing this extremely useful extension for us. There was a thread on mozillazine about SuperDragandGo not working with FF2, a while back (a month?) and someone posted a fixed version, based off 2.4 I recall. I don't believe it was you, but I can't find that thread with the search easily right now.\nI've switched from Super Drag'n'Go to Drag de Go. It's kept up to date and has far far more configuration and gesture options. You can configure searching gestures, too.","processed_text":"@joser916: Have you tried installing the version linked a mere three posts above?\nit works hell ya i got my lil toy back!\nSomething aint right. I updated Firefox 1.5.0.1. Had to make Super D&G compatible. Wheras it worked fine before the Firefox update, I had to diable it cos it kept causing Firefox to freeze which in turn caused everything else to lock up. About 6 manual reeboots later only by disabling this one extension did everything else work OK. Boy, I miss this extension - it was sooooooooo good. Update please!\nI want to replace default directional search engines with my favorite ones.\nI've changed superdragandgo-0.2.6.xpi to superdragandgo-0.2.6.zip -> unpacked -> 'chrome' folder -> changed superdrag.jar to superdrag.zip -> unpacked -> 'content' folder -> edited superdrag.js -> what is next?\nI've tried to create .zip and then change to .jar but seems it doesn't work since when installing I get an error: Install script not found. How to create .jar file?\nrozin wrote: I want to replace default directional search engines with my favorite ones.\nA .jar file is just a .zip file with a different extension.\n1. Did you put the .jar file back in the chrome directory of the .XPI file?\n2. Did you accidentally delete the install.rdf and\/or chrome.manifest file that should exist in the root of the .XPI file?\nYou should put things back EXACTLY where you found them. The directory structure is very important.\nAs I've mentioned in some other thread, (generic) you should use a shell extension or utility like WinZIP or WinRAR that makes .ZIP (and hence .JAR and .XPI) archives look like regular subdirectories. This way you can see where exactly you are drag'n'dropping things. I use Total Commander personally.\nforeword: i posted this on the website on the formular, but the text seemed not to be formatted, so i came here and posted it -formatted- again.\n-same as above for text.\nplease tell me, what do you think.\nThere is a bug dragging links formatted as . See testcase here.\nFor Super DragAndGo on Mac OS X, Is there a special format in specifying the directory where 'dragged' images are saved? This is when bypassing the 'use download manager' option in the preferences.\nI've tried different combinations of filepaths with preceding slashes\/drivenames\/etc and I'm having no luck.\nHow do I disable drag to left open in background and right foreground, which it seems to only do to images.\nIt seems that the searchbox API has been totally reworked in Firefox 2, and as a result, SDAG's drag-to-search feature is broken with Firefox 2. I took 0.2.6 (non-directional) and redid the drag-and-search code so that it works now with Firefox 2's new searchbox implementation.\nCan somebody please do as code65536 mentions on that web page (code diffs, etc.) and find a good version of the directional SuperDragandGo with security patch and apply his modifications to make it work with Firefox 2? If someone does so it could probably be hosted on that same site and people would have their choice of if they want directional or not.\nP.S. Thanks very much code65536 for fixing this extremely useful extension for us. There was a thread on mozillazine about SuperDragandGo not working with FF2, a while back (a month?) and someone posted a fixed version, based off 2.4 I recall. I don't believe it was you, but I can't find that thread with the search easily right now.\nI've switched from Super Drag'n'Go to Drag de Go. It's kept up to date and has far far more configuration and gesture options. You can configure searching gestures, too."}
